# Drizzle Migration Discipline

- When changing persisted data shape, update `db/schema.ts` and generate a migration with Drizzle.
- Keep Supabase runtime SQL companion changes aligned (e.g. `db/policies.sql` for RLS/auth FK constraints).
- Keep schema, model contracts, mapper functions, and repository logic aligned in the same change set.
- Avoid schema-only or UI-only partial changes that break contract parity.
- Prefer explicit migration files over ad-hoc runtime adjustments.
- For relationship changes, verify delete/archive semantics and dependent record handling.
